18:50.318 --> 18:56.087
What you deserve, he said, I will take on me, and he didn't just cover over your sin.

18:56.147 --> 19:06.183
He satisfied the divine wrath of God, and when he was all done, he said, it is finished, your debt is paid in full.

19:08.166 --> 19:10.930
I don't know about you, but every time I think about it,

19:13.602 --> 19:17.066
Every time I think about it, it doesn't make sense to me.

19:18.228 --> 19:21.051
The Bible says, this is the love that transcends understanding.

19:21.091 --> 19:23.835
Why did Jesus die for me?

19:25.176 --> 19:26.638
He died for me when I didn't care about him.

19:27.820 --> 19:29.462
He died for me when I was blaspheming him.

19:29.502 --> 19:31.664
He was dying for me when I was doing all the things.

19:31.764 --> 19:33.427
And he dies for me even when I stumble today.

19:33.487 --> 19:35.549
He does that for me.

19:35.609 --> 19:40.055
And I don't really completely understand that kind of love, but it's changed my life.

19:41.216 --> 19:42.738
And I think it's changed some of your lives.

19:43.394 --> 19:44.376
And so what do we do?

19:45.517 --> 19:52.087
How do we respond to this beautiful, generous legacy?

19:52.127 --> 19:53.910
John, the disciple of Jesus would write this.

19:54.010 --> 20:01.722
He himself, Jesus, is the sacrifice that atones for our sins, and not only for our sins, but for the sins of all the world.

20:03.705 --> 20:05.748
The atonement.

20:05.768 --> 20:07.711
Now here's a theological idea.

20:07.811 --> 20:09.554
Atonement doesn't just mean

20:10.434 --> 20:12.978
like an animal is sacrificed to cover the sin.

20:12.998 --> 20:15.843
It means to fully satisfy or absorb the wrath of God.

20:16.283 --> 20:19.328
You see, when Jesus died on the cross, He paid for all of your passions.

20:21.071 --> 20:22.694
He paid for all of your presence sins.

20:23.515 --> 20:24.857
And He paid for all of your future sins.

20:24.897 --> 20:33.351
The Bible calls it a once and for all sacrifice to bring redemption to all who would come, all who would trust, all who would believe.

20:33.411 --> 20:35.695
And we get to celebrate that today in communion.

20:36.616 --> 20:37.778
Communion, we get to take

20:37.986 --> 20:40.269
a piece of bread and a cup.

20:40.369 --> 20:44.595
And remember that his body was broken for us, his blood was spilled for us.

20:45.096 --> 20:48.240
He got what we deserve, our punishments so that we could go free.

20:48.280 --> 20:51.324
And this is the generosity of our God.

20:51.344 --> 20:57.072
And this story of David points to that moment in the future.

20:58.454 --> 21:02.299
Now, what's the greatest expression of God's love?

21:02.339 --> 21:04.242
Well, Jesus described it this way.

21:05.026 --> 21:09.751
God so loved the world that He gave.

21:11.413 --> 21:13.856
God is generous.

21:15.017 --> 21:18.661
In the very heart of God, in the very nature of God, is a generosity.

21:18.901 --> 21:28.431
And love is expressed through His generosity in all of these ways, in all of David's life, in my life, in our redemption, in our salvation.

21:28.472 --> 21:34.418
And so I want us to think about David's response to the generosity of God.

21:35.522 --> 21:40.248
In a simple statement, it is, I'm not gonna offer back to God something that costs me nothing.

21:41.189 --> 21:45.154
For all that he's done for me, I want this response to go back to him.

21:45.174 --> 21:47.177
I want him to know what's in my heart.

21:47.197 --> 21:59.813
And so as we look at this closing chapter in the books of First and Second, I wanna talk about just two takeaways that we can apply to our lives now as New Testament Christians here in 2025.

21:59.853 --> 22:00.454
Here's the first one.

22:00.554 --> 22:03.698
We have received a generous legacy.

22:04.834 --> 22:05.935
So let's just think for a moment.

22:05.975 --> 22:10.740
How has God been generous to you?

22:17.388 --> 22:21.793
Well, you were created in the very image of God before you were ever born.

22:22.313 --> 22:23.534
He gave you gifts and abilities.

22:23.555 --> 22:24.756
He gave you experiences.

22:24.776 --> 22:25.577
You were born to the family.

22:25.597 --> 22:26.037
You were born to you.

22:26.057 --> 22:26.838
You got the education.

22:26.858 --> 22:28.120
You had the break.

22:28.140 --> 22:29.321
Someone opened that door for you.

22:29.942 --> 22:32.004
Listen, you are not a self-made man.

22:32.044 --> 22:34.066
You're not a self-made woman.

22:34.210 --> 22:40.397
All that you have has been given to you by God, the brain that you have, the house that you have, the relationships that you have.

22:41.878 --> 22:53.511
And the sooner you get ahold of that, you're like, even my calling and my purpose and the way that God's spirit works in me, he saved me, he forgave me, he gave me a calling, he gave me peace, he gives me joy, he heals my diseases.

22:53.531 --> 22:59.197
I mean, you could go on and on and on and on and on and just think about how good and gracious and generous God has been to you.

22:59.838 --> 23:03.922
Because if not, you just simply take for granted

23:05.026 --> 23:06.948
God exists that He loves you.

23:06.968 --> 23:09.390
And that when you say, no, He's got grace.

23:09.410 --> 23:10.411
Forgive me and we move on.

23:10.431 --> 23:16.417
And we don't think about what it costs God to lavish His generosity on us.

23:17.798 --> 23:26.847
But the reality is the more we can think about it and meditate and the more it causes us to instinctively worship and to live in generosity.

23:27.068 --> 23:28.889
And so we've received a generous legacy.

23:28.929 --> 23:31.772
And number two, generosity is our response.

23:33.194 --> 23:33.714
David's.

23:33.826 --> 23:34.227
He says it.

23:34.267 --> 23:37.171
I'm not going to sacrifice the Lord something that costs me nothing.

23:38.352 --> 23:41.557
He's not going to say, well, what's the best price I can get, Arana?

23:42.218 --> 23:46.343
I want to get a discount on this altar because I don't want to give a lot of my money away.

23:46.363 --> 23:47.645
I want to keep as much as I can.

23:47.665 --> 23:51.871
So what's the least amount I can pay you so I can honor God at this place?

23:51.891 --> 23:53.173
Now, David's not thinking that at all.

23:53.193 --> 23:54.855
He's saying, I did a stupid thing.

23:54.875 --> 23:56.397
I deserve judgment.

23:56.477 --> 23:59.942
God's about to show me mercy, whatever it takes, because you've been so generous to me.

23:59.962 --> 24:02.706
This is his heart.

24:02.850 --> 24:07.456
And this practice of learning how to be generous back when you really stop and think what Jesus did for you.

24:08.237 --> 24:13.624
Well, this generosity is not necessarily a natural thing, but it's a supernatural work that God can do in your heart.

24:14.745 --> 24:24.117
Because I remember as a brand new Christian, 18 years old, hearing about this idea that as Christians, we give back to God as he gives us things, resources, finances, we give back to him.

24:25.499 --> 24:28.924
And I was like, I didn't really grow up in a church when they talked about that kind of stuff.

24:28.984 --> 24:30.866
And so the first time I thought about it, I'm like,

24:31.714 --> 24:34.378
That's a lot of money, and that's my money.

24:36.000 --> 24:47.438
And I remember the first time I was challenged to give to a church or give to sponsor kids who were hungry in another country, and it was like the most painful experience, because I was saying goodbye to a little bit of my control.

24:49.040 --> 24:51.464
You see, let's just think about this.

24:51.484 --> 25:00.978
If I keep all my money to myself, then I have like an insulation between me and a crisis so that I don't really need God, I've got money in the bank.

25:01.506 --> 25:07.114
Like for David, if he has a sense that he has 1.3 million people, he doesn't really need God, because his soldiers can defend him.

25:07.295 --> 25:09.138
And then if that doesn't work out, he can pray, God help me.

25:10.119 --> 25:12.162
But God doesn't want to be number two on your lists.

25:13.504 --> 25:15.387
That's why Jesus said, you can't serve God and money.

25:15.407 --> 25:15.788
Pick one.

25:16.709 --> 25:20.635
And if you pick God, he will bless you abundantly, but as you give, he will fill your empty hand.

25:20.655 --> 25:22.398
This is how a relationship goes, right?

25:22.418 --> 25:27.646
He's not, he is not interested in a transaction.

25:28.807 --> 25:30.610
He's not even interested in the amount.

25:31.426 --> 25:35.510
He's interested in the heart and the way that it builds this relationship.

25:36.491 --> 25:42.358
And so I remember it took me a minute before I could give and experience a smile.

25:43.359 --> 25:45.461
You know, sometimes you do the right thing, even if you're not feeling it.

25:45.481 --> 25:47.443
Nobody?

25:47.463 --> 25:48.785
Okay.

25:48.805 --> 25:50.126
Too honest, people just greet your teeth.

25:50.146 --> 25:50.827
This is the right thing.

25:50.867 --> 25:51.428
I'm going to obey.

25:51.508 --> 25:52.068
I'm going to do it.

25:52.148 --> 25:57.394
And I can say in the first year I gave, I was not experiencing joy.

25:58.882 --> 26:03.667
but I met some people here at this church who helped form this joy in me and taught me.

26:03.727 --> 26:10.394
As we raised our kids, we would teach our kids to get your allowance, it's a dollar, you had 10 dimes, give the first dime to God, to his people.

26:10.434 --> 26:13.817
And then you'll always have more than enough, and so our kids grew up this way.

26:13.877 --> 26:17.761
And sometimes you know how your kids can teach you about the joy of giving?

26:17.781 --> 26:23.907
I mean, I remember my oldest son, Jackson, he loved balloons, and one day we bought him this red balloon.

26:24.448 --> 26:26.770
He's like four or five years old, we walk outside,

26:28.258 --> 26:30.381
He lets it go, and I'm like, well, I just paid for that balloon.

26:32.084 --> 26:33.385
And he's like, this is for you, Jesus.

26:35.168 --> 26:37.231
And that red balloon, I was like, it's $5.

26:37.291 --> 26:38.213
What's he doing?

26:39.795 --> 26:45.744
And I was like, my five-year-old son is teaching me about the heart of generosity.

26:46.585 --> 26:51.352
I love this balloon, but Jesus, I want you to have it.

26:51.372 --> 26:53.575
You can learn a lot from a five-year-old about generosity.

26:55.017 --> 26:55.698
You see?

26:56.098 --> 26:59.002
this idea of generosity being our response.

26:59.062 --> 27:00.785
It's not natural, but it's supernatural.

27:00.805 --> 27:03.609
Listen, we are made in the image of a God who is generous.

27:04.871 --> 27:09.878
And so you're never gonna be more like God, more like his son Jesus, than when you're generous.

27:10.959 --> 27:12.702
And so how does this shape us?

27:12.722 --> 27:15.426
How does it shape our hearts as a people?

27:15.866 --> 27:18.650
Because we want to be like Jesus.

27:20.092 --> 27:24.018
And again, this goes against all of our instincts for self-sufficiency.

27:25.090 --> 27:48.254
all of our instincts for will of people know how much money I have or what kind of car I drive or what kind of house I live in or where I vacation or if people know the latest device I have, I'll get respect or off security in case something really bad happens and Jesus offers us those costumes that the wisest way we can live is in generous response to the generous legacy we have received.

27:49.435 --> 27:52.338
And so I want us to think for a moment about our present moment.

27:53.218 --> 27:55.901
This weekend is gonna be a mark in our spiritual history.

27:56.902 --> 28:02.489
I love that our young people, our high school and middle school students are in the room because you're gonna witness something that's gonna be a generational moment.

28:02.509 --> 28:05.172
We've only done this once or twice in the first 40 years of Calvary.

28:05.192 --> 28:08.336
We're gonna make an offering to the Lord.

28:08.396 --> 28:10.559
And here's what I want you to think about.

28:11.700 --> 28:20.210
All of this, the whole idea of Calvary, the whole idea of a church started here, started 40 years ago with a few people in a small church in Las Vegas

28:20.770 --> 28:23.693
And we don't even know most of these people's names, but I'm gonna show you this picture.

28:23.753 --> 28:26.236
This is our origin story of our church 40 years ago.

28:26.256 --> 28:32.663
40 years ago in this small church in Las Vegas, there were four people who said, we believe we should go to Fort Lauderdale, Florida and plant a church.

28:34.004 --> 28:35.586
And this small church prayed over them.

28:35.966 --> 28:39.170
And if you notice in the bottom left-hand corner, there's a bucket.

28:39.190 --> 28:41.813
It says gifts for Fort Lauderdale.

28:41.833 --> 28:47.018
And so the people in that church, they took some money out of their pockets or wrote a check and put in that bucket.

28:47.038 --> 28:50.322
And everything that you know that is Calvary Chapel,

28:51.330 --> 29:07.252
Calvary Chapelwood, four kids, Calvary Christian Academy, Calvary House, and 58 church plants across the world, 60,000 people who have come to know Jesus, 30,000 in Baptist, all those things started in that bucket, right?

29:08.815 --> 29:14.042
And so we've been telling that story for the last 40 days.

29:14.062 --> 29:16.946
We've been talking to our leaders, like if all that happened from

29:17.282 --> 29:23.950
the legacy of the first generation of Calvary, and now we're entering the next 40 years, then how can we be generous toward the next generation?

29:23.990 --> 29:32.119
Because right now, we are literally enjoying the generosity, the prayers, and the sacrifice of that previous generation.

29:33.600 --> 29:39.347
And so, I want us to talk about this moment, because this is not a moment that we do a lot at Calvary.

29:39.407 --> 29:42.390
Frankly, at Calvary, here's what we do, or here's how we talk about giving.

29:42.410 --> 29:45.714
We say, generosity is a response, it's an act of worship,

29:45.922 --> 29:49.888
So there are boxes in the back and you can give your ties and offerings.

29:49.908 --> 29:51.291
You can give them online.

29:51.311 --> 29:54.656
There are different ways to give, but we don't make a big deal out of it.

29:54.696 --> 29:59.363
Definitely not a public deal out of it because we want there to be an honor.

29:59.443 --> 30:03.310
As you get to know Jesus more, he shapes your heart more and more toward generosity.

30:04.191 --> 30:06.755
We don't talk about it as a law like the Old Testament type.

30:06.835 --> 30:08.658
The Bible talks about the grace of giving.

30:09.506 --> 30:17.195
That that giving the first and best 10% is just the beginning of how God shapes your heart toward generosity, toward his work and his people.

30:18.156 --> 30:28.888
And so when we think about a public giving moment, well, certain verses come in my mind like, wait, didn't Jesus say, don't let your left hand know what your right hand gives?

30:29.168 --> 30:30.450
Shouldn't this be anonymous?

30:30.510 --> 30:37.618
And Jesus did say that in the Sermon on the Mount, but I'll give you some context for what he says and why he says it.

30:38.402 --> 30:48.595
You see, in those three pastures, he says, when you fast and when you pray and when you give, don't do it to be seen by other people.

30:49.396 --> 30:57.747
In other words, don't draw attention to yourself, don't make a show, don't be thinking, oh, someone's gonna see how holy I am by praying this prayer.

30:57.767 --> 30:59.910
Someone's gonna see how generous I am by giving this money.

30:59.930 --> 31:02.653
Someone's gonna see how spiritual I am because I haven't eaten enough.

31:02.673 --> 31:04.556
I've been fasting and I'm telling everyone I'm fasting.

31:04.876 --> 31:06.418
If you're gonna do those things,

31:06.978 --> 31:09.101
Don't do it to draw attention to yourself.

31:09.281 --> 31:11.525
But Jesus is not prohibiting public prayer.

31:11.665 --> 31:13.167
We pray all the time publicly.

31:13.928 --> 31:16.131
He's not prohibiting public fasting.

31:16.171 --> 31:19.376
We call fasts and people have called fasts all through the Bible.

31:19.396 --> 31:25.004
And he's not prohibiting public giving because public giving was part of both the Old Testament and the New Testament.

31:26.246 --> 31:29.090
But Jesus is also saying this, it's not about the amount you give.

31:29.871 --> 31:34.898
You see, the only time Jesus pointed someone out in a public giving moment

31:35.106 --> 31:37.610
was a woman who gave just like two pennies.

31:37.670 --> 31:40.235
It was a poor widow in the back of the church that no one else saw.

31:41.296 --> 31:42.458
Giving is not about the amount.

31:42.478 --> 31:49.851
Listen, whether you give $2 or $2 million, your name is not gonna end up on a plaque.

31:49.871 --> 31:52.636
It's not gonna end up on this back wall because there's only one name here.

31:52.676 --> 31:54.419
We're gonna honor his name as Jesus, right?

31:54.439 --> 31:56.863
So it's not about you.

31:56.983 --> 32:01.170
It's about a family, a group of people coming together and say,

32:01.314 --> 32:02.556
He is worth it.

32:02.756 --> 32:06.442
Here's what he's done for us, and here is our grateful response.

32:07.344 --> 32:15.797
And so in a moment, we're gonna do that, but I wanna just share with you some principles from the three public offerings that we see in the Bible, two from the Old Testament and one from the new.

32:16.418 --> 32:28.658
And we're gonna go back to our bookshelf because we've been talking about all the stories that God has written here at Calvary, but we're gonna go way back in time to the book of Exodus, written at the time of Moses,

32:29.506 --> 32:31.829
And Moses calls for a public offering.

32:31.869 --> 32:34.353
He says, we want to build God a tabernacle.

32:34.373 --> 32:45.527
God has given me in my mind this space where we can meet with God, where the Ark of the Covenant will be, where there'll be these places where we can wash our hands and meet with God and eat the show bread.

32:45.548 --> 32:47.270
And there's this beautiful invitation.

32:48.031 --> 32:55.120
And so he invites people, bring your jewelry, bring your cloth, bring your precious stones, and bring it as an offering to God.

32:56.082 --> 32:59.346
Now, the thing about a public offering is God

32:59.810 --> 33:04.235
always calls for one after he's done something generous first.

33:04.315 --> 33:05.716
So where did these people come from?

33:06.878 --> 33:09.000
These people that are about to make this offering.

33:09.040 --> 33:13.164
Well, they were in slavery for 400 years before this offering.

33:13.645 --> 33:16.328
They cried out to God, God show us mercy, show up, deliver us.

33:16.568 --> 33:22.034
And God brought Moses and brought the plagues and delivered them through the Red Sea and swallowed up their enemy on the way out.

33:22.695 --> 33:25.738
And then he brought bread from heaven and water from Iraq.

33:26.819 --> 33:29.682
And now he says, bring your offerings.

33:31.074 --> 33:48.914
And here's the response.

33:49.154 --> 33:53.399
And those who are willing and those who are willing, and they came and they brought joyfully.

33:53.679 --> 34:00.568
And this is the only offering in the entire Bible and in the entire history of the world that I know of where the leaders had to say, stop bringing stuff.

34:00.728 --> 34:01.849
We already have more than enough.

34:03.471 --> 34:09.919
I've never ever heard of that ever again, but most of like guys, we have too much gold and too much jewelry and too much cloth.

34:09.979 --> 34:11.060
We can't use anymore.

34:12.462 --> 34:14.905
Now, I have a question.

34:15.605 --> 34:16.146
Think with me.

34:16.738 --> 34:22.544
Where did these Hebrew slaves get this jewelry from and this gold from and this precious stones and this cloth from?

34:23.365 --> 34:24.767
They were slaves for 400 years.

34:26.228 --> 34:32.615
Oh, on the way out of Egypt, the Egyptians gave them all the stuff that said, get out, go with your God and leave.

34:32.935 --> 34:36.079
And the Israelites received all of this great wealth.

34:36.239 --> 34:39.643
People who've been slaves for 400 years are now wealthy beyond their imagination.

34:39.863 --> 34:46.610
And I'm just thinking of I'm like an Israelite and I got this massive gold ring and it looked good on me.

34:47.266 --> 34:50.970
I was a slave for 400 years, or my family's wearing out, now I've got this beautiful gold ring.

34:51.831 --> 34:59.961
And now I hear Moses say, if you want to bring in your gold and offer it to God of a choice, man, I love this ring.

35:02.383 --> 35:03.384
And that's always the choice.

35:04.486 --> 35:08.370
Would I willingly and joyfully give what I love as a sack price?

35:08.390 --> 35:10.332
Because I don't want to offer it to God, something that costs me nothing.

35:10.573 --> 35:12.054
I want to give this gold to them.

35:12.074 --> 35:15.218
And if I'm one of those Israelite men or women, and I see the gold

35:16.578 --> 35:17.820
that's arraying all this.

35:18.040 --> 35:18.741
I was a part of that.

35:18.761 --> 35:19.281
I can say, you know what?

35:19.301 --> 35:20.663
I got to be a part of what God did.

35:20.703 --> 35:22.165
I got to respond to what He did to me.

35:22.245 --> 35:33.699
And I don't think any of us ever want to be the people that let everyone else enjoy the blessing of giving and building something and going, and this brings us to this next moment.

35:34.240 --> 35:39.026
You see, after David built or David created or bought this

35:39.714 --> 35:42.298
Threshing in Florida, then there's a chance now to build.

35:42.318 --> 35:46.724
He's 70 years old, and he's gonna say, hey, on this threshing floor, we're gonna build the temple.

35:47.285 --> 35:54.615
This thing I had a dream about, and he tells the people, as he gathers this great assembly, he says, God put this in my mind, but told me I couldn't build it.

35:54.635 --> 36:05.190
So I've gathered all the workers, I've gathered all the gold jewels we have now, the location where the temple's gonna be built, and I'm gonna give out of my own personal treasure.

36:05.270 --> 36:08.274
Not just out of the national treasure, but out of my own personal treasure.

36:08.386 --> 36:09.728
And then he asked this question.

36:10.269 --> 36:15.697
He says to all the leaders and whoever else is willing, you can consecrate yourself, you can give with us.

36:16.699 --> 36:23.228
And then the people watched as David gave, as the leaders gave, and they gave willingly and joyfully.

36:23.248 --> 36:29.638
And there's this incredible celebration as the temple plans are about to be put into place and the temple's about to be built.

36:29.658 --> 36:34.405
And then David breaks out in a song because that's what he always does.

36:34.465 --> 36:37.650
And here's his song, First Chronicles.

36:37.986 --> 36:38.767
Chapter 29.

36:40.650 --> 36:47.519
Yours Lord is the greatness and the power and the glory and the majesty and the splendor for everything in heaven and earth is yours.

36:48.701 --> 36:49.742
Yours Lord is the kingdom.

36:50.403 --> 36:52.486
You're exalted as head over all.

36:52.546 --> 36:53.948
Wealth and honor come from you.

36:54.769 --> 36:55.971
You are the ruler of all things.

36:56.251 --> 37:00.577
In your hands are strength and power to exalt and give strength to all.

37:01.959 --> 37:02.560
And here it comes.

37:03.541 --> 37:04.402
But who am I?

37:05.474 --> 37:08.920
And who are my people that we should be able to give as generously as this?

37:10.042 --> 37:14.169
Everything comes from you, and we have given you only what comes from your hand.

37:15.551 --> 37:23.545
So Lord our God, all this abundance that we have provided for building you a temple for your holy name comes from your hand, and all of it belongs to you.

37:23.585 --> 37:29.074
And I know, my God, that you test the heart and are pleased with integrity.

37:29.922 --> 37:33.327
All these things I have given willingly and with honest intent.

